Josephine Stampfer, Respondent v. Siegmund, alias William Stampfer, Appellant. Decided November 3, 1890. Appeal from an order granting plaintiff an allowance for counsel fee. Louis Ansbacher, for appellant. Samuel D. Sewards, for respondent.

Before Freedman, Truax and Ingraham. JJ.

Per Curiam.

The order was reversed and motion denied, without costs, on the authority of Beadelston v. Beadelston, 103 N. Y. 402.
